# Finn's AI Reef — optional environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env.development.local` (for `npm run dev`) and/or
# `.env.production.local` (for `npm run build`), then fill in the values.
# Those *.local files are git-ignored and are NOT overwritten by `rayfin env`.
#
# ── Azure AI Speech (human, soothing neural voice) ─────────────────────────
# When set, Finn's "Read to me" uses an Azure neural voice (e.g. Sonia) instead
# of the robotic browser voice. Leave blank to fall back to browser voices.
#
#   Create a Speech resource in the Azure portal, then copy its Key and Region.
#   Region examples: uksouth, westeurope, eastus.
#   Voice examples: en-GB-SoniaNeural, en-GB-LibbyNeural, en-US-AriaNeural,
#                   en-US-JennyNeural.
#
VITE_AZURE_SPEECH_KEY=
VITE_AZURE_SPEECH_REGION=
VITE_AZURE_SPEECH_VOICE=en-GB-SoniaNeural

# Optional: only for custom-subdomain / private-endpoint / Foundry resources.
# A standard resource needs REGION only — leave this blank.
# VITE_AZURE_SPEECH_ENDPOINT=
